import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    data_grouped = data.groupby('year')['fertility'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data_grouped['year'], data_grouped['fertility'], label='Fertility Rate')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.title('What is the trend of fertility rate over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'], c=data['year'].dt.year, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between fertility rate and life expectancy?', wrap=True)

    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Years")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('country')['fertility'].max().sort_values(ascending=False)
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 6), color='blue')
    max_fertility = data.max()
    ax.axhline(max_fertility, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Fertility: {max_fertility:.2f}')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.title('Which country has the highest fertility rate?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['life_expect'].plot.hist(bins=20, alpha=0.5, color='blue', label='Life Expectancy')
    plt.axvline(data['life_expect'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['life_expect'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for country in data['country'].unique():
        country_data = data[data['country'] == country]
        ax.plot(country_data['year'], country_data['n_fertility'], label=country)

    ax.axhline(data['n_fertility'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['n_fertility'].median():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.3, 1))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("How does the change in fertility rate compare to the previous year?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
